climbs.name: Crack Problem
climbs.fa: N/A - Old rock I'm sure someone climbed it

content.description: Start with your left hand in the crack and your right hand on the crimp.  Use the crack for your feet and head all the way up, top out to the left.  After the crack the top out rock is gritty

Starts deep in the wide crack.  Rock below you on the ground and the face to the right are off.  Climb out of the crack and around the horn to top out. 

  Caution: the is a nice fin on the right side of the horn.  DO NOT USE THIS.  It's getting a bit loose and could probably break.
content.location: Boulder at far left of Overlook Wall.  It sticks out towards the trail.

content.description:
Central fairly featureless face with a crack up the middle and a boulder out left. The right face has some TR opportunities. Directly off the trail, below the Overlook.

 There seems to be some park users that like to toss trash/broken glass/etc. out here. Please help keep this area clean and grab something as you leave.
